      "content": "Your feelings of existential dread and loss of identity are profound, and it makes sense that concepts like \"rest\" feel impossible when the source of your purpose has vanished. Many people experience a similar \"midlife purgery\" where the roles they built their lives around dissolve, leaving them feeling unmoored and haunted by their own existence. While this pain warrants professional support, try to approach it not as the first step toward \"nothing,\" but as a necessary, albeit terrifying, foundation for rebuilding a self outside of your work identity.",
      "source": "target",
